description:
William Miller grew up with a Patriot father and a preacher’s daughter for a mother. He was taught the love of country and the love of Christ. He carried the thirst for knowledge he had as a child into adulthood, leading him to precious new discoveries that would impact generations of Christians, including Seventh-day Adventists. 

Tune in to Lest We Forget with Jonathan Burt as host and Jim Nix as tour guide, to remember the important history leading to the Adventist movement, which today includes more than 21 million souls. 
__________________________________________________

The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are believers who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing, and hope in Jesus.

Want to learn more about the Seventh-day Adventist Church? 
Visit our website at: https://www.adventist.org/
